{"questionId":"9074575","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A fixed horizontal coil is connected to an ideal voltmeter. A bar magnet is released from rest&nbsp;so that it falls vertically through the coil along the central axis of the coil.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/dfa3ef167876d20762e3cee7114564b45ae0374b.png\"></p>\n<p>The variation with time<em> t</em> of the emf induced in the coil is shown.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/368f95f6f4d9a84d04e52b5e491b54b5877c824b.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the fundamental SI unit for your answer to (a)(i).</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>kg m<sup>2 </sup>A<sup>−1 </sup>s<sup>−3</sup> ✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074575","referenceCode":"22M.2.HL.TZ2.a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the fundamental SI unit for your answer to (a)(i).","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.1 – Electromagnetic induction","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.1 – Measurements in physics","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}